title: Scene03_Dialogue
---
Narrator: The fog has grown thicker by the time MC returns to Saint Bartholomew’s Infirmary. The lamps outside burn low, their light trembling against the wet stone. Inside, the halls are quieter than before.

Narrator: A nurse stops as soon as she sees him.

Nurse: My lord? What do you have need of us at this hour?

Edmund: I need my medical records.

Nurse: Your records?

Edmund: They called me a counterfeit at my own gate. If the Trial demands proof, then my body will provide it.

Nurse: But the archive has been sealed.

Edmund: Sealed?

Nurse: Court officers came shortly after your departure. No record bearing your name is to be released before the Trial.

Edmund: So first they accuse me, and now lock away my own defense.

Nurse: I am sorry, my lord.

Nurse: ...

Narrator: The nurse’s eyes drifted to his neck, to the old scar trailing toward his shoulder, a mark he had borne since childhood.

Nurse: That burn, It was I who dressed that when you were so little.

Edmund: Then you know it is mine.

Nurse: I remember a frightened boy with your face.

Edmund: I need to regain my identity. Please, tell me where the records are kept?

Narrator: Her eyes roll downward, as if she is fighting her own reason.

Nurse: Below this ward. But the door leading there is pressure-bound. The officers sealed the steam flow before they left. Without it, the door will not open.

Edmund: Then I will restore the pressure.

Nurse: But without proper knowledge, restoring the steam flow is extremely dangerous. If you do it wrong, the line will not be the only thing that bursts. I cannot let you...

Narrator: Her eyes, filled with concern, focus on the mark on his shoulder again.

Edmund: My lady, by dawn I may not legally exist anymore. Danger can wait.

Narrator: The nurse hesitates, then lowers her voice.

Nurse: There is an old service stair behind the apothecary room. It leads beneath the ward.

Edmund: Thank you.

Nurse: ...

Nurse: My lord...

Nurse: If you find what you came here for, please be certain you are ready.

Edmund: ...!?


===
